# Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge - Working for Mubo[]

In the year 34aby an Unidentified droid repair technician woke up on Mubo's Cargo Tansport. The droid tech was greeted by a droid named J-4X, who told them to get to work in the cargo hold. The Droid Technician made their way towards the cargo hold, where they received a call from Mubo on their DataGrip. Mubo told them what to do, and the Droid Tech went to the cargo hold to scan all the cargo, and received a Hoverpack When finished, the cargo was marked done, and a ship was signaled to pick it up, but it exploded due to blaster fire from a Guavian Ship. The Guavians subsequently boarded the freighter, and the droid tech went to find a blaster, and used it to shoot guavian death gang hellions and Hunters. The droid tech won the blaster fight, and received a message from the Guavians Leader Tara Rashin, who told them that the first order was paying lots of money for a piece of cargo Mubo was smuggling, and told the droid tech to stand down and surrender. Tara also shot J-4X. The droid tech fought a few more guavian death gang members, and was told by Mubo to jettison the cargo, so they did that, and then made their way to the escape pods. After shooting more Guavians they escaped from the ship, and landed on Batuu.
metadata.title: Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge

vectors.title: Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge

categories: Articles with an excess of redlinks
metadata.content:
# Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge - Searching for the Cargo[]

The Droid repair technician made their way to Seezelslak's Cantina where they met Seezelslak. Mubo walked in with his droid assistant R00-8Y, and told the technician that the cargo they had jettisoned was scattered around Batuu and their next job would be to find it. The technician went to the Three Suns Overlook, and began searching, but soon more guavian death gang members. They also get a call from Mubo telling them that the shipment contained prototype Mini-droids, and it was that is was also his job to find them. The Droid Technician stumbled upon some of the cargo, but it was guarded by Guavians, so after a brief shoot out, they moved on, searching for  the one piece of cargo that Tara had said the first order was willing to pay for. Along the way, they encountered many little stores of weapons and Training Remotes that were also from Mubo's cargo ship, and they put them to good use against the Guavians. They also encountered Viper probe droids and Seeker droids under the control of the Guavians. Eventually the droid technician makes it past the Guavians, and goes to Dead Root Refuge to continue their search for the cargo.
metadata.title: Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge

metadata.content:
# Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge - Fighting Tara[]

While at Mubo's Workshop, C-3PO Intercepted a transmission from the Guavian Death Gang that said they have R2-D2, so the droid technician set out with 3PO to find R2. Howere While in Dead Root Refuge, C-3PO fell down a hole, and the droid tech was forced to go on without him. After fighting their way through Dead Root Refuge again, they reunited with C-3PO who had found his way out of the hole and to the door leading to Tara. They both attempt to open the door, but a TT-8L gatekeeper droid blocked their entrance. C-3PO attempted to reason with the droid, but while doing so, they were attacked. The Droid Tech fended off the attackers while C-3PO Convinced the droid to open the door, and they both stepped into the elevator. They emerged at the Splintered Spire, and at first, saw the place deserted. They found R2-D2's crate, and rescued him, but then, Tara emerged riding an All Terrain Reconnaissance Transport. She was accompanied by a few other Guavian Death Gang members, but the Droid Tech took care of them quickly. However, normal blasters could not pierce the shield around Tara's Walker. The Droid Tech kept her distracted, and dodge the rockets she sent, while R2 used the central computer to release explosive barrels from their container. The Barrels rolled down near the walker, and exploded, setting it off Ballance, and tumbling down the spire, never to be seen again. They all returned to safely Seezelslaks Cantina.
metadata.title: Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge

metadata.content:
# Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy's Edge - Dead Root Refuge and Hissiq Springs[]

After arriving in Dead Root Refuge, the droid technician battled more Guavian Death Gang members in search of the cargo. They found more cargo, but not the one that Mubo needs most desperately. So they continued on to Hissiq Springs, where the Guavians had gathered in even more force. A fierce fire fight ensued, but eventually, the droid technician made it into the caves. Once out of the caves, they fought more Guavian Death Gang members, but eventually find the cargo Mubo was looking for. Inside the crate, they found C-3PO, but his Photoreceptor was dangling out of it's socket, and he was missing a leg an arm, and a hand. He instructed the droid tech to go look for them, and they so they did. They had to fight more Guavians to get the pieces, but once they were all recovered, the droid tech returned and repaired C-3PO. C-3PO then opened R2-D2's Container, but R2 was missing. Then C-3PO fell out of the cargo container as the door closed behind him. The Droid Technician was forced to find another way to get to C-3PO, and has to fight more Guavians, but is eventually reunited with the droid. Then, they both head back to Mubo's Workshop.
metadata.section: Dead Root Refuge and Hissiq Springs[]

Nikto mechanics

Chronological & political information

[Source]


A pair of male Kajain'sa'Niktos were members of Kidd Kareen's Podracer crew around 22 BBY. They and the rest of Kareen's crew agreed with San Maxus to start helping the Separatists and Count Dooku in order to make enough money to retire from podracing all together. While working on Mon Gazza the Niktos aided Maxus and the other mechanics in fending off the undercover Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker, as Skywalker had been snooping around Kidd Kareen's pit looking for Separatist contraband. Kareen arrived shortly after the fight began and broke it up. Later Skywalker again confronted Maxus as he was making a pitstop during the Mon Gazza Maze, in attempt to grab Republic intel from Maxus who was going to sell it to Asajj Ventress. Maxus escaped, leaving Skywalker to face the Niktos and the rest of the crew yet again. Anakin was able to dispatch some of the mechanics with debris, including one of the Niktos, but left to pursue his Padawan Ahsoka Tano, who was podracing. This left the clone trooper Rex and the droid R2-D2 to fend off the remaining mechanics and Nikto. Later, Kareen indicated that after it all only Maxus had been retired from the crew after being killed by Ahsoka Tano. Kareen in fact offered Tano to take a job as a replacement for Maxus, but Tano refused.
metadata.title: Unidentified Nikto mechanics (Mon Gazza)

metadata.content:
# Batuu Jedi temple meditation chamber - History[]

Around 379 BBY, Jedi Padawan Rooper Nitani went to the chamber to meditate after she was unable to shake a feeling of anticipation. While meditating, she reached out with the Force, perceiving the life around her as glowing colors and sensing other Jedi in the temple, including Petrish Imglor, Evat Seth, and her Master, Silandra Sho. She then reached out further, and sensed a flock of skylar-birds, a herd of horned stoans, and the forests surrounding the temple, before losing her concentration.

Just as Nitani was considering seeking counsel from her Master, Sho entered the room with the church droid P3-7A and explained that the anticipation Nitani was sensing was actually her own. When Nitani questioned her, Sho told her that it was now time for Nitani to undergo her Jedi Trials to become a Jedi Knight. Sho explained that she had hidden her shield, which Nitani would have to find, and also told her to take P3-7A with her, although the droid knew nothing about the shield's location. Nitani then left the room with P3-7A to begin searching.

After Nitani found the shield, she returned to the meditation chamber, where Sho was waiting. Nitani told her about what had happened during her trials, and they agreed to talk to the Jedi Council the next day. As Sho left the room, Nitani attempted to return the shield to her, but Sho told her to keep it and explained that she wanted to honor the tradition of passing down the shield from Master to Padawan.
metadata.title: Batuu Jedi temple meditation chamber

# Batuu Jedi temple - Life on the frontier[]

In 382 BBY, after a mission to the planet Gloam, Rooper Nitani travelled to Batuu and spent time in the archives reading journals and holobooks to better prepare for her future missions on the Galactic Frontier. Merak was a Gran Jedi Master who served as the archivist of the Batuu Jedi temple archive.

# Batuu Jedi temple meditation chamber - Description[]

A meditation chamber was located in the Jedi Order's Batuu Jedi temple. There was a mat on the floor of the room that Jedi could sit on while meditating. The chamber had a doorway that led to a corridor.
metadata.title: Batuu Jedi temple meditation chamber

metadata.content:
# Batuu - Guavian Death Gang raid[]

In 34 ABY, a freighter owned by Droid Depot's Mubo was attacked by the Guavian Death Gang, led by Quarren pirate Tara Rashin. A droid repair technician managed to escape by crash-landing on Batuu. The technician, running errands for cantina owner Seezelslak, defeated the Guavian Death Gang members who landed on the planet and retrieved some of Mubo's lost cargo.
metadata.title: Batuu

metadata.content:
# Laser Masters

Laser Masters


Publication information

Release date
By 19 BBY


Type
Show


[Source]

Laser Masters was a program that Imperial officer Canonhaus loved watching as a child before the Galactic Empire's founding in 19 BBY. Canonhaus had hazy memories of the show, which he remembered as if from another reality and thought that it would not be approved by the Empire's Commission for the Preservation of the New Order.

In one of the later episodes of Laser Masters, the Senate chamber was defended by a Laser Master from an army of monsters, and before his final stand, the Master uttered "none shall pass" as his last words. The Laser Master's last words remained in Canonhaus' mind as his Imperial Star Destroyer traversed the Hoth asteroid belt as part of Death Squadron in 3 ABY, hoping that none of the asteroid fragments would penetrate his ship's deflector shields. However, during Canonhaus' holographic meeting with Darth Vader and other Death Squadron commanding officers, an asteroid flew into Canonhaus' Star Destroyer, obliterating its bridge and killing the officer.
metadata.title: Laser Masters

metadata.content:
# Senya Tirall - Equipment[]

Senya had a unique blue-bladed lightsaber pike where the hilt could be extended anytime she wanted. Her lightsaber was made of an alloy called Phrik, which was resistant to lightsabers. She also carried a standard single-bladed lightsaber.
metadata.title: Senya Tirall

Marcie was the name given to a blue-bladed lightsaber owned by Jedi Knight Rissa Mano. During the heat of a battle while on a mission to Hissrich, Mano briefly lent Marcie to Mace Windu, allowing him to use it along with his own lightsaber to take down a harvester.
metadata.title: Marcie

metadata.content:
# Marcie - History[]

At some point, Mano practiced deflecting blaster bolts with Marcie. In 22 BBY, Jedi Master Mace Windu chose recent Jedi Knight Mano to accompany him—along with Jedi Council member Kit Fisto and Jedi Prosset Dibs—to an operation on the jungle planet Hissrich, which Mano brought Marcie along to. After arriving on the planet aboard a T-6 shuttle the Westwind, the group traveled west through towards the Separatist outpost. Along the way, the group encountered a patrol squadron of the droid unit stationed on Hissrich.
metadata.title: Marcie
